In declarative approach we put all the details in yaml document and we pass it on to kuberntes cluster , Cluser takes care 
of creating the resources accourdingly.

# kubectl run nginx --image='nginx:latest' --port=80 --dry-run=client -o yaml> test.yaml
To expose the port 
# kubectl expose pod nginx --port=80 --type=NodePort --dry-run=client -o yaml > svc.yaml

The above command will create yaml file with specified configuration after that 

# kubectl create -f nginx.yml --> The command itself we are not giving all the details , it will detect it from yaml file , ceate a resource and read every thing from
yaml document. 
To check the status 
# kubectl get pod 
TO test and validate 
# kubectl port-forward pod/nginx 8080:80 

Suppose something went wrong we need to troubeshoot 
1)  # kubectl logs nginx -- The log comming from nginx pod 
# kubectl logs nginx --previous

2) sometime we need to go inside the pod to troubleshooting 
# kubectl  exec -it nginx -- bash 
> ls 
> exit

TO delete the pod 
# kubectl delete pod nginx 






  





